<subSubSection pageId="123" pageNumber="124" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="123" pageNumber="124">
94b. 
<taxonomicName LSID="57F419C2-5F48-589D-B9CF-3C673BF0599D" authority="(Verdc.) J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" authorityName="(Verdc.) J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Verdc." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus capituliferus subsp. foliaceus" order="Solanales" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="capituliferus" status="stat. nov." subSpecies="foliaceus">Convolvulus capituliferus subsp. foliaceus (Verdc.) J.R.I.Wood &amp; R.W.Scotland</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="123" pageNumber="124">stat. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="123" pageNumber="124" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="123" pageNumber="124">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wood &amp; Williams &amp; Mitchell &amp; Carine &amp; Harris &amp; Scotland" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus capituliferus subsp. var. var. foliaceus" order="Solanales" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="capituliferus" status="stat. nov." subSpecies="var." variety="foliaceus">Convolvulus capituliferus var. foliaceus</taxonomicName>
Verdc., Kew Bull. 37: 462. 1982. (
<bibRefCitation author="Verdcourt, B" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="213" pageNumber="214" pagination="459 - 464" publicationUrl="10.2307/4110047" refId="B375" refString="Verdcourt, B, 1982. Corrections and additions to the &quot;Flora of Tropical East Africa: Convolvulaceae &quot; V. Kew Bulletin 37: 459 - 464, DOI: 10.2307/4110047" title="Corrections and additions to the &quot; Flora of Tropical East Africa: Convolvulaceae &quot; V." url="10.2307/4110047" volume="37" year="1982">Verdcourt 1982</bibRefCitation>
: 462). Type. KENYA, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Kirrika</emphasis>
140 (K).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="123" pageNumber="124" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="123" pageNumber="124">
Based on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wood &amp; Williams &amp; Mitchell &amp; Carine &amp; Harris &amp; Scotland" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus capituliferus subsp. var. var. foliaceus" order="Solanales" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="capituliferus" subSpecies="var." variety="foliaceus">Convolvulus capituliferus var. foliaceus</taxonomicName>
Verdc.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="123" pageNumber="124" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Leaves and bracts 3-6 cm long giving the inflorescence a leafy appearance. Corolla 9-12 mm long.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="123" pageNumber="124" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="123" pageNumber="124">
This seems to be the only subspecies in Kenya (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Gillett</emphasis>
21325, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Padwa</emphasis>
194) and Ethiopia (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Ellis</emphasis>
232, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">de Wilde</emphasis>
5909) but also occurs in Somalia (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Hemming &amp; Deshmukh Jess</emphasis>
298).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="123" pageNumber="124" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="123" pageNumber="124">
Distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hochst. ex Choisy, Prodr. [A. P. de Candolle] 9: 405. (Choisy" authorityYear="1845" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus rhyniospermus" order="Solanales" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhyniospermus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Convolvulus rhyniospermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the larger, easily visible, shallowly lobed, blue corolla. 
<bibRefCitation author="Thulin, M" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Somalia" pageId="212" pageNumber="213" pagination="232 - 237" refId="B360" refString="Thulin, M, 2006. Convolvulus. Flora of Somalia volume 3: 232 - 237" title="Convolvulus." volume="volume 3" year="2006">Thulin (2006</bibRefCitation>
: 235) treated this species as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hochst. ex Choisy, Prodr. [A. P. de Candolle] 9: 405. (Choisy" authorityYear="1845" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus rhyniospermus" order="Solanales" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhyniospermus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Convolvulus rhyniospermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but 
<bibRefCitation author="Verdcourt, B" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="213" pageNumber="214" pagination="459 - 464" publicationUrl="10.2307/4110047" refId="B375" refString="Verdcourt, B, 1982. Corrections and additions to the &quot;Flora of Tropical East Africa: Convolvulaceae &quot; V. Kew Bulletin 37: 459 - 464, DOI: 10.2307/4110047" title="Corrections and additions to the &quot; Flora of Tropical East Africa: Convolvulaceae &quot; V." url="10.2307/4110047" volume="37" year="1982">Verdcourt (1982</bibRefCitation>
: 459) drew attention to the distinctive characters of the two species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
